headline: The AI End for Software and Services Stocks Isn’t Nigh. Companies Are Fighting Back.
summary: It might be time to pause the funeral dirge for software and services stocks. Artificial intelligence hasn’t killed them after all.  In fact, companies are going out of their way to remind investors that AI is as much an opportunity as it is an existential threat.  When design software developer  Figma  reported earnings Wednesday, it stressed that its own AI tools and partnerships with ChatGPT owner OpenAI and Gemini parent  Alphabet  were boosting customer retention figures.

headline: Moody's Riyadh Move Highlights Middle East Growth Ambitions And Valuation Tension

The move deepens the company's presence in the Middle East and supports Saudi Arabia's Vision 2030 initiative. The Riyadh hub is intended to strengthen engagement with local institutions and capital markets.
